ActiveDirectorySubnetCollection Class

In this Article

    public System.DirectoryServices.ActiveDirectory.ActiveDirectorySubnet this[int index] { get; set; }

    Parameters

    • index
      Int32

      The zero-based index of the ActiveDirectorySubnet object to get or set.

    Property Value

    • ActiveDirectorySubnet

      The ActiveDirectorySubnet object that exists at the specified index.

    Exceptions

    • ArgumentException

      The member already exists in this collection (applies to set only).

    • ArgumentNullException

      The item specified is null (applies to set only).

    • ArgumentOutOfRangeException

      The index specified is out of range of this collection.

    • InvalidOperationException

      The ActiveDirectorySubnet specified has not yet been saved to the Active Directory Domain Services store (applies to set only).
